WEBVTT

00:10.445 --> 00:13.622
Maggie, this is serious.
You have a stalker.

00:13.665 --> 00:15.885
Previously on
"A Million Little Things"...

00:15.928 --> 00:16.929
I'm -- I'm Eddie.

00:16.973 --> 00:18.018
Anna: I'm Anna.

00:19.236 --> 00:20.281
How do you know Sophie?

00:20.324 --> 00:21.630
I'm Anna Benoit.

00:21.673 --> 00:22.979
Sophie: Peter's wife.

00:23.023 --> 00:24.459
Anna:
I'm trying to move on,

00:24.502 --> 00:27.462
but Peter's taking
even that away from me.

00:27.505 --> 00:29.159
I'm ready for my audition.

00:29.203 --> 00:31.379
Paragon Plus is giving you
your movie back.

00:31.422 --> 00:32.510
Really?

00:32.554 --> 00:35.035
Look at that.
We were supposed to meet.

00:35.078 --> 00:37.254
Hi.It just felt like
I'd been away long enough.

00:37.298 --> 00:38.342
Is that okay?

00:38.386 --> 00:39.909
I don't think
we can do this.

00:41.128 --> 00:43.478
Can we talk to you
about something?

00:43.521 --> 00:45.610
And suddenly the woman
you thought you were gonna

00:45.654 --> 00:48.048
spend the rest of your life
with is having another baby

00:48.091 --> 00:51.051
with a man who spells
"Stephen" with a P-H!

00:51.094 --> 00:53.618
I think I know who's been
sending me these letters.

00:53.662 --> 00:54.924
He died three years ago.

00:56.230 --> 01:03.193
♪♪

01:03.237 --> 01:10.331
♪♪

01:10.374 --> 01:11.897
Make any sense of
it yet?

01:11.941 --> 01:14.683
It looks like
a bunch of pages

01:14.726 --> 01:17.729
that were torn out of
Justin's journals.

01:17.773 --> 01:19.122
I put some of them
in order,

01:19.166 --> 01:20.776
but there are just
still these huge gaps.

01:20.819 --> 01:23.083
As far as I can tell,
they were all written

01:23.126 --> 01:24.910
right after he stopped
coming to see me.

01:26.173 --> 01:28.088
He was so talented.

01:28.131 --> 01:29.480
I mean, this looks
just like you.

01:29.524 --> 01:31.569
Yeah, he was a student
at the Art Institute.

01:31.613 --> 01:33.658
One of my first clients,
right out of grad school.

01:33.702 --> 01:35.530
What happened to him?

01:35.573 --> 01:37.488
I'm sorry. You --
You don't have to talk about it.

01:37.532 --> 01:40.143
No, it's okay.
Um...

01:40.187 --> 01:43.233
He was going through
some really hard stuff

01:43.277 --> 01:47.368
and eventually, he started
having feelings for me.

01:47.411 --> 01:49.152
We're trained to deal with
that kind of thing,

01:49.196 --> 01:51.198
but when I tried to
talk to him about it,

01:51.241 --> 01:53.678
he just stopped showing up
for his appointments.

01:53.722 --> 01:58.292
I reached out to him,
but I never heard back.

01:58.335 --> 02:00.859
And a few months later,

02:00.903 --> 02:03.645
I found out that
he had taken his life.

02:04.733 --> 02:06.082
I'm so sorry.

02:07.257 --> 02:10.173
But if he's gone,
who's sending you these?

02:10.217 --> 02:12.306
Whoever's got his journal.

02:12.349 --> 02:15.613
They're obviously still grieving
and need help.

02:15.657 --> 02:18.790
I feel terrible for them.

02:18.834 --> 02:21.750
You feel bad for the stalker
who's tormenting you,

02:21.793 --> 02:24.709
which makes you officially
the best person I've ever met.

02:24.753 --> 02:29.018
Tell that to the small but
very vocal group of Bruins fans

02:29.061 --> 02:31.063
who think it's my fault
you lost last night.

02:31.107 --> 02:33.501
Well, you did steal my energy
before the game.

02:33.544 --> 02:35.111
Hmm.
But we need more data,

02:35.155 --> 02:36.982
which is why,
in the name of science,

02:37.026 --> 02:39.724
I suggest that we rerun
the experiment

02:39.768 --> 02:41.248
before my flight to New York
tonight.

02:41.291 --> 02:43.554
Oh, well, if it's
in the name of science.

02:43.598 --> 02:45.165
You're a doctor.

02:45.208 --> 02:46.383
It seems like you have
an obligation.

02:46.427 --> 02:47.341
Mm-hmm.

02:47.384 --> 02:49.734
♪♪

02:49.778 --> 02:51.040
Can't wait.

02:51.083 --> 02:53.695
[ Cellphone chimes ]Oh, and I am late.

02:53.738 --> 02:55.958
Uh, I'm gonna stop by that
poké place that we like

02:56.001 --> 02:57.481
on my way home.
Mm!

02:57.525 --> 03:00.397
So just text me
what you want.

03:00.441 --> 03:01.746
Alright, love ya.

03:01.790 --> 03:04.314
♪♪

03:04.358 --> 03:07.578
Please note, I said
"love ya," not "love you."

03:07.622 --> 03:08.840
[ Chuckles ]
Which everybody knows

03:08.884 --> 03:10.886
are completely different
things.Totally.

03:10.929 --> 03:13.149
Not that I don't love you,
'cause I do love you.

03:13.193 --> 03:17.066
I mean,
like I love all humanity.

03:17.109 --> 03:20.765
Uh, I think what
I meant to say was...peace!

03:20.809 --> 03:22.071
[ Door closes ]

03:22.114 --> 03:23.115
Peace ya.

03:23.159 --> 03:25.161
♪♪

03:30.862 --> 03:32.124
Good morning, sunshine.

03:32.168 --> 03:34.779
Ah, you're up early.
Would you like some coffee?

03:34.823 --> 03:36.607
Nah, I am fueled by

03:36.651 --> 03:38.914
the righteous pursuit
of self-improvement.

03:38.957 --> 03:41.264
Oh.
Dr. Jessica says
time to let go

03:41.308 --> 03:43.005
of all things
me and Darcy,

03:43.048 --> 03:46.008
so I am cleaning out
what I have left.

03:46.051 --> 03:47.749
Where are you off to
so early?

03:47.792 --> 03:49.446
Sophie's audition
for MMI is today.

03:51.013 --> 03:52.144
Oh, that's great.

03:52.188 --> 03:54.190
Yeah. She wants me to
give her notes

03:54.234 --> 03:56.323
on her new song,
and then Regina and I

03:56.366 --> 03:57.802
are going with her
in the afternoon.

03:59.151 --> 04:00.283
So she only invited
the people

04:00.327 --> 04:02.720
who haven't
massively failed her.

04:02.764 --> 04:04.331
That makes sense.

04:04.374 --> 04:06.463
I'm pretty sure a year ago,
I'd be persona non grata, too.

04:06.507 --> 04:08.465
And I have the smashed guitars
to prove it.

04:10.554 --> 04:12.339
She'll forgive you.
It just takes time.

04:12.382 --> 04:14.036
Yeah.

04:14.079 --> 04:16.604
And Dr. Jessica said
I have to let go

04:16.647 --> 04:19.302
of the things I can't control
and try to forgive myself.

04:19.346 --> 04:22.392
She also said that I have
to stop being the person

04:22.436 --> 04:24.916
that starts every sentence
with "Dr. Jessica said."

04:24.960 --> 04:26.701
Well, it sounds like
you're making progress.

04:26.744 --> 04:29.312
Dr. Jessica said I am.[ Chuckles ]

04:29.356 --> 04:31.140
Alright, man.
See you later.

04:31.183 --> 04:34.578
Wish her luck for me,
silently,

04:34.622 --> 04:37.625
so that hearing my name
does not throw her off her game.

04:37.668 --> 04:38.800
Will do.

04:39.801 --> 04:41.106
[ Door closes ]

04:41.150 --> 04:43.848
♪♪

04:43.892 --> 04:45.197
Hey.

04:45.241 --> 04:49.680
♪♪

04:49.724 --> 04:51.465
Oh, babe,
I have morning breath.

04:51.508 --> 04:53.336
I missed
your morning breath.

04:53.380 --> 04:55.338
[ Chuckling ]
Okay, but I gotta get up.

04:55.382 --> 04:57.035
[ Chuckling ]
That's what I'm trying to do.

04:57.079 --> 04:58.994
But I really have to go.

04:59.037 --> 05:00.430
It's been six months

05:00.474 --> 05:01.779
since we've been in
our own bed together,

05:01.823 --> 05:03.999
and last night
we were so tired.

05:04.042 --> 05:07.959
Mm-hmm.[ Cellphone vibrating ]

05:08.003 --> 05:10.179
Oh, I'm sorry.
I'm sorry.
Mnh-mnh.

05:10.222 --> 05:11.789
Yeah, you know what?
I should -- I should get that.

05:11.833 --> 05:13.269
That's Cassandra.
She's probably calling about

05:13.313 --> 05:14.531
our pitch to PBS today.

05:16.141 --> 05:18.709
Hey, there.
No, no. It's perfect timing.

05:18.753 --> 05:21.146
I just gotta figure out what
I'm wearing to this meeting.

05:21.190 --> 05:24.149
[ Guitar playing ]

05:24.193 --> 05:29.503
♪♪

05:29.546 --> 05:31.548
Soph...

05:31.592 --> 05:32.941
it's incredible.

05:32.984 --> 05:35.204
[ Laughs ]
It's good, right?

05:35.247 --> 05:36.684
[ Laughs ]

05:36.727 --> 05:38.990
I'm just a little worried
about auditioning with it.

05:39.034 --> 05:41.123
Might be a little edgy
for MMI.

05:41.166 --> 05:42.777
All of the best art
comes from

05:42.820 --> 05:44.518
channeling your most powerful
emotions,

05:44.561 --> 05:45.736
like Alanis.

05:45.780 --> 05:47.216
She's the queen of that.

05:47.259 --> 05:49.174
Well, I got my inspiration
from what Anna said.

05:50.785 --> 05:52.047
Thinking about Peter

05:52.090 --> 05:54.702
and everything he took
from both of us,

05:54.745 --> 05:56.704
it just clicked.

05:56.747 --> 05:59.489
Well, I'm just glad something
good came out of that night.

05:59.533 --> 06:01.665
Yeah, that must have been
a pretty terrible first date.

06:01.709 --> 06:03.101
[ Chuckles ]
[ Sighs ]

06:03.145 --> 06:04.494
Are you gonna see her
again?

06:04.538 --> 06:06.322
No, definitely not.

06:06.366 --> 06:08.672
We both agree
it's too complicated.

06:08.716 --> 06:10.674
When has that
ever stopped you?

06:10.718 --> 06:13.329
Alright.

06:13.373 --> 06:14.896
I deserved that.

06:14.939 --> 06:16.898
[ Chuckles ]

06:16.941 --> 06:22.294
But if my relationship with
your mom taught me anything,

06:22.338 --> 06:25.689
it's that if it starts messy,
it stays messy.

06:25.733 --> 06:27.604
That's catchy.

06:27.648 --> 06:29.432
Maybe I'll use that
for my next hook.

06:29.476 --> 06:31.173
Well, clearly my work here
is done.

06:31.216 --> 06:32.522
[ Chuckles ]

06:32.566 --> 06:35.133
[ Refrigerator beeping ]

06:42.880 --> 06:44.316
[ Beeping stops ]

06:46.841 --> 06:53.108
♪♪

06:53.151 --> 06:55.066
Ed, I don't know
what's going on,

06:55.110 --> 06:56.416
but if I need to
close my eyes

06:56.459 --> 06:57.765
and leave the apartment
immediately,

06:57.808 --> 06:59.506
just say the word.

06:59.549 --> 07:08.863
♪♪

07:08.906 --> 07:10.908
Liam.

07:10.952 --> 07:13.258
[ Chuckling ]
Hey, you found your hat!

07:13.302 --> 07:14.738
Yeah.

07:14.782 --> 07:16.261
What are you doing here,
pal?

07:16.305 --> 07:17.611
Following your lead.

07:17.654 --> 07:19.526
Lenox sucks,

07:19.569 --> 07:23.094
so just gonna
live here with you now.

07:23.138 --> 07:24.748
Hey, can I make you
a sandwich?

07:24.792 --> 07:28.970
♪♪

07:29.013 --> 07:30.972
Dr. Jessica is not
gonna like this.

07:35.672 --> 07:39.197
[ Ringing]

07:39.241 --> 07:40.938
Darcy: Hey, it's Darcy.
Leave a message.

07:40.982 --> 07:41.722
[ Sighs ][ Beeps]

07:41.765 --> 07:43.985
Hey, Darce.

07:44.028 --> 07:45.334
I don't know
how to say this

07:45.377 --> 07:47.684
without sounding like
a kidnapper, but, uh...

07:47.728 --> 07:50.382
I have your son.

07:50.426 --> 07:52.907
Oh, no, no, no.
You're right. You're right.

07:52.950 --> 07:56.388
The blue vest looked sharp.
Yeah.

07:56.432 --> 07:59.261
Okay.
I'll see you there.

07:59.304 --> 08:00.741
How's Cassandra?

08:00.784 --> 08:02.569
Oh, she's good. Just giving me
some notes on our pitch.

08:02.612 --> 08:04.222
She really knows
her stuff.

08:04.266 --> 08:05.354
Apparently.

08:06.790 --> 08:09.271
And she seems to know
what you look good in, too.

08:09.314 --> 08:11.099
[ Scoffs ]
What's that supposed to mean?

08:11.142 --> 08:14.885
Nothing, just picking up
on a vibe, that's all.

08:14.929 --> 08:17.148
A vibe?
[ Chuckles ] Yeah.

08:17.192 --> 08:18.541
I mean,
I wouldn't be surprised

08:18.585 --> 08:20.543
if she had
a little crush on you.

08:20.587 --> 08:22.589
I mean, who can blame her?
I have a crush on you, too.

08:22.632 --> 08:24.199
Are you for real?

08:25.983 --> 08:27.985
You know, thanks to Cassandra,
my film's getting a second life.

08:28.029 --> 08:30.118
No, it --
it totally should.

08:30.161 --> 08:33.338
I'm just pointing out
your energy

08:33.382 --> 08:34.949
when you talk to her
on the phone, that's all.

08:34.992 --> 08:36.820
Okay, so -- so what -- what
are you really saying, Gina?

08:36.864 --> 08:38.343
D-D-Do you not trust me?

08:40.389 --> 08:43.348
Of course
I trust you.

08:43.392 --> 08:45.786
Look, I'm glad she's helping
you. I just --

08:45.829 --> 08:47.396
Cassandra believes in
my film,

08:47.439 --> 08:48.832
so she's using
her connections

08:48.876 --> 08:50.268
to get it back out there
again,

08:50.312 --> 08:53.097
but if you want me to stop
working with her, say that.

08:53.141 --> 08:56.579
No, of course not.
[ Sighs ]

08:56.623 --> 09:00.452
I -- Look, just forget I even
brought it up, okay?

09:00.496 --> 09:02.324
Great.
Already forgotten.

09:02.367 --> 09:08.156
♪♪

09:08.199 --> 09:10.332
[ Door opens ]What the -- [ Sighs ]

09:10.375 --> 09:12.377
[ Door closes ]

09:12.421 --> 09:15.032
You know the last time I played
this game was with you?

09:15.076 --> 09:17.208
I'm still kicking
your butt.

09:17.252 --> 09:20.255
Man: Score!Goaaaaalllll! Again.

09:20.298 --> 09:21.909
Alright, let's rematch?

09:21.952 --> 09:24.346
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Hold up.
Hold up. Hold up.

09:24.389 --> 09:27.262
Talk to me. What's going on?
Why are you really here?

09:29.394 --> 09:32.441
I already told you.
I hate Lenox.

09:32.484 --> 09:33.921
It's in the middle of
nowhere.

09:33.964 --> 09:37.098
There's nothing to do.
And...

09:37.141 --> 09:40.231
I just...feel like
I'm always in the way,

09:40.275 --> 09:43.583
so I just took my skateboard
and left.

09:43.626 --> 09:45.759
What do you mean, you --
you feel like you're in the way?

09:45.802 --> 09:48.152
[ Sighs ] It's just...

09:48.196 --> 09:50.154
everything's about
the baby now.

09:50.198 --> 09:52.287
Ah.

09:52.330 --> 09:53.723
Huh.

09:53.767 --> 09:55.377
Well, sure, sure.

09:55.420 --> 09:57.597
But aren't you excited about
being a big brother?

09:57.640 --> 10:02.210
I thought I was,
but in the past couple days,

10:02.253 --> 10:04.647
I feel like they'd be
better off without me,

10:04.691 --> 10:07.258
so I thought maybe I could
come stay with you, instead.

10:07.302 --> 10:08.651
[ Knock on door ]

10:08.695 --> 10:11.436
[ Sighs ]

10:11.480 --> 10:12.437
That's your mom.

10:12.481 --> 10:14.309
Wait, wait.
You called my mom?

10:14.352 --> 10:17.704
I had to, pal.
No, no. She --
She can't be here.

10:17.747 --> 10:20.010
She can and she is.

10:22.709 --> 10:23.884
You're not Darcy.

10:23.927 --> 10:25.450
And you're not Liam.

10:25.494 --> 10:26.364
I'm Gary.

10:26.408 --> 10:27.670
I'm Stephen.

10:27.714 --> 10:29.759
I'm all caught up.

10:29.803 --> 10:32.283
Thanks so much
for calling us.

10:32.327 --> 10:34.895
Come on, Liam!

10:34.938 --> 10:36.592
Darcy didn't tell me
youwere coming.

10:36.636 --> 10:39.160
Or that, apparently,
she has a beard fetish.

10:39.203 --> 10:41.075
Now I'm questioning
everything.

10:41.118 --> 10:43.773
[ Door closes, lock clicks ]Liam: I can't believe
you called my dad!

10:43.817 --> 10:45.253
You're such a traitor!

10:45.296 --> 10:46.689
Come on, pal.

10:46.733 --> 10:48.038
Leave me alone!

10:48.082 --> 10:51.172
[ Knob rattles ]Liam!

10:51.215 --> 10:53.217
Kids. [ Chuckles ]
Am I right?

10:54.741 --> 10:56.307
Dale: Okay, just tell me,

10:56.351 --> 10:58.135
was Cam in a good mood
this morning?

10:58.179 --> 11:00.355
Did he get a full 8 hours
of sleep?

11:00.398 --> 11:02.096
Do you think he can
cover the spread?

11:02.139 --> 11:04.576
'Cause if I don't win back the
1,000 bucks I lost last game,

11:04.620 --> 11:06.056
my wife's gonna kill me.

11:08.450 --> 11:10.278
What I'm hearing is that

11:10.321 --> 11:13.847
you express your passion
for the Bruins

11:13.890 --> 11:16.371
through an unhealthy
gambling habit.

11:16.414 --> 11:18.721
It's only unhealthy
if I lose!

11:18.765 --> 11:20.288
Am I gonna lose?

11:20.331 --> 11:21.942
Stay on the line,
Dale,

11:21.985 --> 11:24.031
and I will have Claudia
share

11:24.074 --> 11:26.337
some helpful resources
with you.

11:26.381 --> 11:30.385
Meredith from Albany,
having problems at work.

11:30.428 --> 11:34.432
Hello, Meredith from Albany.
You are in the room.

11:34.476 --> 11:35.825
Meredith: Dr. Bloom?

11:35.869 --> 11:38.306
Yes. I hear you're having
some problems at work.

11:38.349 --> 11:40.569
Yeah, that's what I told
your screener,

11:40.612 --> 11:42.440
but the real reason I'm calling
is because

11:42.484 --> 11:44.355
I want every one of
your listeners to know

11:44.399 --> 11:46.967
what you did to Justin.

11:47.010 --> 11:49.360
You are a fraud,
Maggie Bloom.

11:49.404 --> 11:50.884
You're up here every day
talking to the masses

11:50.927 --> 11:52.363
like you're some kind of savior

11:52.407 --> 11:54.452
when everyone should
know the truth --

11:54.496 --> 11:58.021
that because of you,
my son is dead.

11:58.065 --> 12:00.981
♪♪

12:05.725 --> 12:07.509
I know you've been
trying to get in touch.

12:07.552 --> 12:09.772
I received your...mail.

12:09.816 --> 12:12.644
Meredith: I wanted you to see
what you did to my son.

12:12.688 --> 12:15.343
Claudia: Maggie,
we should cut this off.

12:15.386 --> 12:18.781
I understand that
you are in pain, Meredith.

12:18.825 --> 12:21.088
Don't you dare tell me
about pain.

12:21.131 --> 12:22.785
I have to sit here every day
and listen

12:22.829 --> 12:26.658
to you pretend to care about
anyone besides yourself,

12:26.702 --> 12:29.879
the way you pretended to care
about Justin.

12:29.923 --> 12:32.490
Jane: Maggie, she's
attacking you. Drop the call.

12:32.534 --> 12:33.753
Tell you what.

12:33.796 --> 12:35.624
Why don't I go to
commercial,

12:35.667 --> 12:38.148
and you and I can
talk about this privately?

12:38.192 --> 12:41.717
Why? So your audience
can't hear the truth?

12:41.761 --> 12:44.024
If you go to commercial,
I'll hang up.

12:44.067 --> 12:47.941
Alright. I understand.
Let's, uh -- Let's talk here.

12:47.984 --> 12:50.204
It's clear that you're
very angry with me,

12:50.247 --> 12:52.815
and I can only imagine
how much you're hurting.

12:52.859 --> 12:54.251
Maggie, commercial, now.

12:54.295 --> 12:55.992
And I know it may be
hard to believe,

12:56.036 --> 12:57.515
but I really do
want to help.

12:57.559 --> 13:00.954
Just stop. Stop pretending like
you're so professional.

13:00.997 --> 13:03.783
I'm the one who found him.

13:03.826 --> 13:08.222
I knew something wasn't right.
A mother just knows.

13:08.265 --> 13:10.441
[ Voice breaking]
So I went to see him.

13:10.485 --> 13:12.530
Do you have any idea
what it's like

13:12.574 --> 13:15.403
to lose a child like that?

13:15.446 --> 13:16.578
No, I don't.

13:16.621 --> 13:18.710
Of course you don't.

13:18.754 --> 13:20.538
Well, I think about it
every single --

13:20.582 --> 13:22.192
[ Beep, click ]

13:22.236 --> 13:23.237
Meredith?

13:25.717 --> 13:27.110
Did you get
her callback number?

13:27.154 --> 13:28.677
♪♪

13:28.720 --> 13:30.548
Take your next call.

13:30.592 --> 13:36.859
♪♪

13:36.903 --> 13:39.644
Meredith, you got cut off.
Please call me back.

13:39.688 --> 13:41.864
♪♪

13:41.908 --> 13:43.213
[ Button clicks ]

13:43.257 --> 13:46.608
Philip in Danvers,
you are in the room.

13:46.651 --> 13:47.870
Philip: Yeah, hi.

13:47.914 --> 13:49.872
Longtime listener,
first time caller.

13:49.916 --> 13:51.918
I was gonna get some advice
about my relationship

13:51.961 --> 13:53.615
with my ex, but...

13:53.658 --> 13:56.531
I gotta ask, was that last
woman telling the truth

13:56.574 --> 13:58.185
about you and her son?

13:58.228 --> 14:02.929
♪♪

14:02.972 --> 14:04.278
[ Sighs ]

14:08.543 --> 14:12.025
Okay, I cannot find
my screwdriver,

14:12.068 --> 14:14.679
but it appears I have
all the components you need

14:14.723 --> 14:17.160
to build a time machine, so
maybe we just do that instead?

14:17.204 --> 14:18.858
How do you lose
a screwdriver?

14:18.901 --> 14:20.120
How do you lose
your son?

14:21.773 --> 14:22.949
I'm sorry.

14:22.992 --> 14:24.298
No,
I probably deserve it.

14:25.690 --> 14:27.040
Things have been
really tough lately,

14:27.083 --> 14:28.432
and you're not exactly
helping.

14:28.476 --> 14:29.912
Whoa.

14:29.956 --> 14:32.915
What I mean is,
it's been tough,

14:32.959 --> 14:35.483
living in the shadow of
Gary Mendez.

14:35.526 --> 14:38.094
All Liam talks about is how good
you are at street hockey,

14:38.138 --> 14:40.053
how fast you can eat
a Philly cheesesteak,

14:40.096 --> 14:42.533
the voices you do
during D&D.

14:42.577 --> 14:45.014
I just don't get it.

14:45.058 --> 14:47.364
He's gotta be the only kid
in the world who's upset

14:47.408 --> 14:49.758
that his mom and dad
managed to work things out.

14:52.152 --> 14:55.068
[ Scoffs ] What am I doing
having another kid?

14:55.111 --> 14:57.157
I can't even take care of
the family that I have.

14:57.200 --> 15:00.116
M-My wife's on bed rest
and my son hates me so much

15:00.160 --> 15:02.336
that he took a bus two hours
to get away.

15:02.379 --> 15:04.947
Darce is on bed rest?
W-- Is everything okay?

15:04.991 --> 15:07.123
She was reorganizing
the laundry room

15:07.167 --> 15:09.256
the other night
when she tripped and fell.

15:09.299 --> 15:10.257
Oh, my God.

15:10.300 --> 15:11.998
I rushed her
to the hospital.

15:12.041 --> 15:13.521
Thankfully, she and the baby
are okay,

15:13.564 --> 15:16.654
but the doctor says that
she has to be off her feet

15:16.698 --> 15:17.960
for the rest of
the pregnancy.

15:18.004 --> 15:19.353
♪♪

15:19.396 --> 15:20.963
How long ago
did this happen?

15:21.007 --> 15:24.401
A couple days. Why?

15:24.445 --> 15:27.100
I think I might know
what's going on with Liam.

15:27.143 --> 15:30.364
♪♪

15:30.407 --> 15:31.495
[ Chuckles ]

15:31.539 --> 15:33.019
[ Typing ]

15:33.062 --> 15:34.629
[ Cellphone swishes ]Who's that?

15:34.672 --> 15:36.979
Oh, it's Morgan from
the open mic.

15:37.023 --> 15:40.548
Her bass guitarist and drummer
are in some huge fight,

15:40.591 --> 15:42.463
and they're taking bets on
who's gonna cave first.

15:42.506 --> 15:44.073
Well, if there's one thing
that's true

15:44.117 --> 15:45.988
regardless of genre,

15:46.032 --> 15:47.685
it is always
the drummer's fault.

15:47.729 --> 15:48.686
[ Chuckles ]

15:48.730 --> 15:50.471
Hi.

15:50.514 --> 15:51.385
Gina!

15:51.428 --> 15:53.517
Hi!

15:54.823 --> 15:56.085
Thank you for being here.

15:56.129 --> 15:58.609
Of course.
I wouldn't miss it.

15:58.653 --> 16:00.785
Hey.[ Chuckles ]
Hi.

16:00.829 --> 16:02.526
♪♪

16:02.570 --> 16:04.485
Hey. What is it?

16:04.528 --> 16:07.227
It's just, uh...

16:07.270 --> 16:10.317
last time I was in this building
was the day I met Peter.

16:10.360 --> 16:12.145
♪♪

16:12.188 --> 16:14.712
Oh, honey.

16:14.756 --> 16:16.323
Yeah, that must be
really intense.

16:16.366 --> 16:17.802
Yeah.

16:19.630 --> 16:21.589
It's also the day
that Gary went off on him.

16:21.632 --> 16:24.113
[ Scoffs ]
Just one in a long line

16:24.157 --> 16:26.898
of many massive
Mendez mistakes.

16:26.942 --> 16:28.596
Actually, that's a good
vocal warm-up --

16:28.639 --> 16:29.814
many massive
Mendez mistakes.

16:29.858 --> 16:31.425
Many massive
Mendez mistakes.

16:31.468 --> 16:33.862
Look, I know this really
isn't the time,

16:33.905 --> 16:36.517
but I just gotta say --

16:36.560 --> 16:40.260
if someone hurt Theo or Charlie
the way Peter hurt you,

16:40.303 --> 16:42.001
I probably would have done
the same thing Gary did.

16:44.264 --> 16:46.483
And if your dad were here,
he would have, too.

16:46.527 --> 16:48.398
♪♪

16:48.442 --> 16:50.879
Gary took my voice away.

16:50.922 --> 16:53.360
My dad never would have
done that.

16:53.403 --> 16:56.537
♪♪

16:56.580 --> 16:58.060
Can you give us a minute?

16:58.104 --> 16:59.322
Sure.

16:59.366 --> 17:02.064
I will go get you
some water.

17:02.108 --> 17:04.197
It's good for
your vocal chords.

17:04.240 --> 17:06.503
Hey.

17:06.547 --> 17:10.072
I want you to acknowledge
how strong you are,

17:10.116 --> 17:11.769
and no matter what the people
in that room

17:11.813 --> 17:14.381
say or don't say,

17:14.424 --> 17:18.689
to come back here, to be
willing to take this chance

17:18.733 --> 17:22.519
after everything
that happened,

17:22.563 --> 17:25.653
I hope you are as proud of
yourself as I am of you.

17:25.696 --> 17:26.958
[ Door opens ]

17:27.002 --> 17:28.569
Professor:
Sophie Dixon?

17:30.527 --> 17:32.486
Now, go take
your voice back.

17:32.529 --> 17:39.101
♪♪

17:39.145 --> 17:45.803
♪♪

17:48.632 --> 17:50.852
♪♪

17:50.895 --> 17:52.897
Peter:
You hit all the right notes.

17:52.941 --> 17:54.812
It just lacked passion.

17:54.856 --> 17:56.336
Music's obviously
a wonderful hobby for you

17:56.379 --> 17:58.251
and -- and I encourage you
to continue it.

17:58.294 --> 18:05.867
♪♪

18:05.910 --> 18:08.391
Uh, excuse me.
Is Dr. Reeves here?

18:08.435 --> 18:10.219
Oh, no.
I'm afraid she's not.

18:10.263 --> 18:11.916
But, uh -- But she was the one
who told me

18:11.960 --> 18:13.092
to come back and audition.

18:13.135 --> 18:14.571
I see.

18:14.615 --> 18:18.053
Well, she just left us
for a position at Berklee.

18:18.097 --> 18:19.315
Oh.

18:21.012 --> 18:22.405
[ Sighs ]

18:22.449 --> 18:25.365
So, what song will you
be playing for us today?

18:25.408 --> 18:28.585
Peter: Can you please tell me
and the other judges

18:28.629 --> 18:30.326
what your piece is about?

18:31.545 --> 18:32.459
It's...

18:32.502 --> 18:34.635
No, Miss Dixon.

18:34.678 --> 18:36.027
♪♪

18:36.071 --> 18:39.030
What is your song about?

18:42.425 --> 18:45.559
It's a song I wrote...

18:45.602 --> 18:47.517
about the man
who assaulted me.

18:47.561 --> 18:52.000
♪♪

18:56.265 --> 19:00.269
♪♪

19:00.313 --> 19:03.838
♪ Did I let me down?

19:03.881 --> 19:06.884
♪ Let you get away

19:06.928 --> 19:09.148
♪ From what I had to say

19:09.191 --> 19:14.153
♪♪

19:14.196 --> 19:17.547
♪ Played me like the pieces

19:17.591 --> 19:20.942
♪ Running everything

19:20.985 --> 19:23.118
♪ A puppet on a string

19:24.511 --> 19:27.949
♪ I let you in

19:27.992 --> 19:31.170
♪ Dancing with a monster

19:31.213 --> 19:34.738
♪ You love to make a mess

19:34.782 --> 19:38.002
♪ Take till
there's nothing left ♪

19:38.046 --> 19:41.441
♪ I am the best part

19:41.484 --> 19:44.879
♪ The blue in the fire

19:44.922 --> 19:48.099
♪ The brilliant sunrise

19:48.143 --> 19:51.668
♪ That burns up a liar

19:51.712 --> 19:54.976
♪ And everything after

19:55.019 --> 19:58.675
♪ Is feeding the flames

19:58.719 --> 20:02.070
♪ You're the disaster

20:02.113 --> 20:06.335
♪ And I am the best part

20:06.379 --> 20:08.642
♪♪

20:08.685 --> 20:10.078
I haven't been
this nervous

20:10.121 --> 20:12.080
since my fourth grade
piano recital.

20:12.123 --> 20:13.429
Peed right through
my pants.

20:13.473 --> 20:15.518
[ Chuckles ]Corduroy's even louder
when it's wet.

20:15.562 --> 20:17.433
It's a good thing
she's not in corduroy.[ Chuckles ]

20:17.477 --> 20:19.392
I'm sure
she's crushing it,

20:19.435 --> 20:21.307
and a lot of that is
thanks to you.

20:21.350 --> 20:23.700
After everything
with Delilah,

20:23.744 --> 20:24.832
I never thought
she and I

20:24.875 --> 20:26.050
would get back to
such a good place.

20:28.662 --> 20:29.793
Can I ask you something?

20:33.754 --> 20:35.582
When you and Delilah...

20:35.625 --> 20:37.366
h-happened,

20:37.410 --> 20:39.107
was it because you were
attracted to her,

20:39.150 --> 20:43.546
or because something was off
between you and Katherine?

20:45.156 --> 20:48.421
[ Sighs ] Honestly?

20:48.464 --> 20:49.900
Both.

20:53.730 --> 20:56.211
Katherine used to
do this thing

20:56.255 --> 20:59.040
every day before
she left for work

20:59.083 --> 21:03.392
where she'd sit on the bed
and kiss me goodbye.

21:03.436 --> 21:06.482
Didn't matter if I was
completely sleeping,

21:06.526 --> 21:10.747
it was 4:00 in the morning,
she'd always do it.

21:10.791 --> 21:16.492
Until one day,
after a, uh...

21:16.536 --> 21:19.626
particularly bad fight
that was totally my fault,

21:19.669 --> 21:22.237
I woke up to the sound
of the door closing behind her.

21:23.804 --> 21:26.676
First time, no kiss.

21:26.720 --> 21:29.766
And the next day,
same thing.

21:29.810 --> 21:31.028
They just stopped.

21:31.072 --> 21:35.032
And the thing that
really scared me

21:35.076 --> 21:37.513
was pretty soon,
I didn't miss it.

21:39.210 --> 21:42.083
That's when I knew.

21:42.126 --> 21:44.041
Why do you ask?

21:44.085 --> 21:47.610
Hmm.
It's just, um...

21:47.654 --> 21:50.134
Rome and I are having
a little trouble

21:50.178 --> 21:55.488
getting back in sync,
and...

21:55.531 --> 21:58.839
I can't help but wonder
if I was gone too long.

21:58.882 --> 22:03.931
Uh,
Gina, I'll just say,

22:03.974 --> 22:06.063
when that happened
with me and Katherine,

22:06.107 --> 22:08.892
we were nowhere near as solid
as you guys.

22:10.894 --> 22:14.333
But maybe you should do
what I didn't --

22:14.376 --> 22:16.509
talk to him about it.

22:16.552 --> 22:19.816
♪♪

22:19.860 --> 22:21.035
[ Door opens ]

22:22.515 --> 22:23.646
[ Gasps ] There she is.

22:25.344 --> 22:27.084
Well?

22:28.390 --> 22:29.957
[ Sighs ]
Those bastards.

22:30.000 --> 22:31.567
No, I-I got in.

22:31.611 --> 22:33.700
Those beautiful bastards!

22:33.743 --> 22:35.658
Congrats!
We knew you'd crush it!

22:35.702 --> 22:37.356
Thank you.[ Grunts ]

22:38.748 --> 22:39.749
Where are
we gonna celebrate?

22:39.793 --> 22:41.142
I know a great
Italian place --

22:41.185 --> 22:43.536
deep-dish pizza,
unlimited garlic knots.

22:43.579 --> 22:45.102
Sounds like you already know
where we're celebrating.

22:45.146 --> 22:47.583
[ Chuckles ] You're right.
Rock star's choice.

22:47.627 --> 22:49.193
No, no, no.
Pizza sounds great.

22:49.237 --> 22:51.108
But can we actually do it
later tonight?

22:51.152 --> 22:52.632
There's somebody I want to
tell I got in.

22:52.675 --> 22:54.024
Your mom.

22:54.068 --> 22:55.765
Okay, two people,

22:55.809 --> 22:57.680
and do not tell my mom
I didn't think of her first.

22:57.724 --> 22:59.116
Our lips, sealed.

22:59.160 --> 23:00.204
Okay.

23:00.248 --> 23:02.206
♪♪

23:02.250 --> 23:03.991
Eddie: But just think,
next time you visit campus,

23:04.034 --> 23:05.906
it's going to be
as a student.

23:05.949 --> 23:07.124
You're going to MMI!

23:07.168 --> 23:09.257
Regina:
[ Laughs ] Yeah, she is.

23:09.300 --> 23:11.999
Fay: Rome and Cassandra,
this was wonderful.

23:12.042 --> 23:14.436
I'll have our business affairs
folks reach out.
Thank you.

23:14.480 --> 23:16.699
You know, I think PBS
is the perfect fit.

23:16.743 --> 23:17.874
Couldn't agree more.

23:17.918 --> 23:19.485
Cassandra: Thank you.We'll be in touch.

23:19.528 --> 23:20.921
Bye.

23:23.750 --> 23:25.273
You were amazing.

23:25.316 --> 23:27.623
Thank you, but this wouldn't
even be possible

23:27.667 --> 23:28.624
if it weren't for you.

23:28.668 --> 23:30.757
Mm.
We make a good team.

23:30.800 --> 23:31.888
We gotta celebrate.

23:31.932 --> 23:33.586
As my grandma always says,

23:33.629 --> 23:35.109
life will give you
a lot of lows,

23:35.152 --> 23:38.068
but when you hit a high,
enjoy it.

23:38.112 --> 23:39.461
Well, I ain't about to
argue with Grandma.

23:39.505 --> 23:40.680
Then champagne it is.

23:40.723 --> 23:42.856
Okay, great.
Let's get the cheap stuff, okay?

23:42.899 --> 23:44.771
This is public broadcasting
money.

23:44.814 --> 23:46.207
Unless Big Bird's
footing the bill.

23:46.250 --> 23:47.513
[ Chuckles ]

23:47.556 --> 23:48.688
♪♪

23:48.731 --> 23:49.776
Liam: Go away!

23:49.819 --> 23:51.299
Liam, it's me.

23:51.342 --> 23:52.996
Can you please open up?

23:53.040 --> 23:55.259
I told you,
I'm not going anywhere.

23:55.303 --> 23:56.478
And you don't have to.

23:56.522 --> 23:58.349
I-I just want to
talk to you for a minute.

23:59.481 --> 24:01.309
It's about your mom's fall.[ Door unlocks ]

24:07.620 --> 24:10.057
Hey. Listen, pal.

24:13.626 --> 24:15.932
You understand that
when Mom fell,

24:15.976 --> 24:19.632
no matter what happened,
it wasn't your fault?

24:19.675 --> 24:22.635
If I hadn't left my skateboard
in the laundry room --

24:22.678 --> 24:24.419
It was an accident.

24:24.463 --> 24:26.290
She could have
tripped on anything.

24:26.334 --> 24:29.859
I mean, her belly's so big,
she can't even see her feet.

24:29.903 --> 24:31.034
[ Chuckles ]

24:31.078 --> 24:32.558
But you don't tell her
I said that.

24:35.517 --> 24:38.128
I really need you at home
to help me take care of Mom

24:38.172 --> 24:39.695
and, pretty soon,

24:39.739 --> 24:41.567
your baby sister.

24:44.874 --> 24:46.397
She's gonna love you.

24:46.441 --> 24:48.095
♪♪

24:48.138 --> 24:49.662
And I love you, too.

24:49.705 --> 24:52.447
♪♪

24:52.491 --> 24:55.450
So what do you say?

24:55.494 --> 24:56.886
Should we head back home?

24:56.930 --> 24:58.409
♪♪

24:58.453 --> 24:59.454
Yeah.

24:59.498 --> 25:02.413
♪♪

25:02.457 --> 25:04.894
Jane: What were you thinking?
You know the rules.

25:04.938 --> 25:07.941
If someone calls in with
a personal attack,

25:07.984 --> 25:09.769
you dump the call.
End of story.

25:09.812 --> 25:11.901
I really thought that
I could help her.

25:11.945 --> 25:13.773
I mean, she's clearly in
a desperate place

25:13.816 --> 25:15.035
and she's confused.

25:15.078 --> 25:15.992
Is she?

25:17.167 --> 25:18.342
What are you asking me?

25:19.387 --> 25:21.781
Is there any truth
to what she said?

25:21.824 --> 25:24.000
No, of course not.

25:24.044 --> 25:27.134
Well, unfortunately, that is
not what our audience heard.

25:27.177 --> 25:30.703
We cannot have them questioning
your credibility.

25:30.746 --> 25:32.356
You're right. Yeah.

25:32.400 --> 25:34.054
I will -- I'll address it

25:34.097 --> 25:35.751
at the top of my show
tomorrow.

25:35.795 --> 25:37.710
No. You're gonna take
the rest of the week off

25:37.753 --> 25:40.060
till things calm down.

25:40.103 --> 25:42.192
Wait, you're pulling me
off the air?

25:43.716 --> 25:46.109
We have plenty of
pre-records ready to go.

25:46.153 --> 25:48.982
♪♪

25:49.025 --> 25:50.549
[ Sighs ]

25:50.592 --> 25:54.596
Use this time off to think about
what really matters --

25:54.640 --> 25:57.425
trying to help the one person
who doesn't want it,

25:57.468 --> 26:00.297
or keeping what you
have built here.

26:00.341 --> 26:01.516
You can't have both.

26:01.560 --> 26:04.867
♪♪

26:04.911 --> 26:08.001
[ Door opens, closes ]

26:12.701 --> 26:13.876
[ Bell dings ]

26:13.920 --> 26:16.749
♪♪

26:16.792 --> 26:18.707
Hey, Anna.

26:18.751 --> 26:21.449
Sophie, hey.

26:21.492 --> 26:24.104
Um, what are you --
what are you doing here?

26:24.147 --> 26:26.497
I came 'cause I wanted
to tell you that...

26:26.541 --> 26:28.064
I was just accepted
to MMI.

26:28.108 --> 26:30.284
That's amazing.
Congratulations.

26:30.327 --> 26:31.938
Thank you.

26:31.981 --> 26:34.244
Actually, the song
that got me in

26:34.288 --> 26:36.159
was inspired by our talk
the other night.

26:36.203 --> 26:37.639
[ Sighs ]

26:37.683 --> 26:40.599
I would -- I would really love
to hear it.

26:40.642 --> 26:41.948
I'd like that.

26:41.991 --> 26:43.645
Oh.
I'm so excited for you.

26:43.689 --> 26:45.473
Getting into MMI,

26:45.516 --> 26:48.824
it was -- it was pretty much
the happiest moment of my life.

26:48.868 --> 26:50.565
I didn't know
you went there.

26:50.609 --> 26:52.349
Yeah, for -- for violin.

26:52.393 --> 26:53.742
Well, do you still play?

26:53.786 --> 26:54.874
No.

26:54.917 --> 26:58.355
Um... [ Sighs ]

26:58.399 --> 27:03.143
Someone convinced me
that I wasn't good enough,

27:03.186 --> 27:05.145
and I was naive enough
to believe him.

27:07.669 --> 27:09.279
Do me a favor?

27:09.323 --> 27:14.981
Promise me that you will
always bet on yourself,

27:15.024 --> 27:17.940
because you are
good enough.

27:17.984 --> 27:20.639
I will. Thank you.

27:20.682 --> 27:22.162
I'll let you
get back to work.

27:22.205 --> 27:23.642
Congratulations.

27:23.685 --> 27:25.731
Thank you.
[ Chuckles ]

27:25.774 --> 27:28.211
Hey, what are you
doing tonight?

27:28.255 --> 27:31.258
♪♪

27:31.301 --> 27:32.825
Maggie:
So then she just cuts me off

27:32.868 --> 27:34.565
and sends me straight
to commercial.

27:34.609 --> 27:38.047
And then Jane told me
to take a week off.

27:38.091 --> 27:39.658
Oh, you got put in
the penalty box.

27:40.833 --> 27:43.009
Now I understand why there's
so much fighting in hockey.

27:43.052 --> 27:44.401
Well, hey,
if you got the week off,

27:44.445 --> 27:45.881
you should come with me
on this road trip.

27:45.925 --> 27:47.448
It'll be fun.

27:47.491 --> 27:50.146
Hotel bathrobes,
hotel room service, hotel sex.

27:50.190 --> 27:53.062
Mm, I'd love to,
but I can't.

27:53.106 --> 27:54.585
Aw, why not?

27:54.629 --> 27:57.284
I mean, it beats sitting home
all week in detention.

27:57.327 --> 27:59.112
Mm.

28:01.288 --> 28:03.507
But you're not sitting at home,
are you?

28:03.551 --> 28:08.643
I Googled her and I found out
where she lives in Albany.

28:08.687 --> 28:10.427
Maggie --
Yeah, I know what
you're gonna say,

28:10.471 --> 28:12.516
but I just really need
to talk to her face-to-face.

28:12.560 --> 28:14.214
I know I can help her.

28:14.257 --> 28:15.650
Well, I want to
go with you.

28:15.694 --> 28:16.956
You can't.

28:16.999 --> 28:19.088
You've played
496 straight games.

28:19.132 --> 28:21.003
497,
but who's counting?

28:21.047 --> 28:24.050
Oh, everyone in Boston.

28:24.093 --> 28:25.660
You can't break that streak
because of me.

28:25.704 --> 28:27.923
I'm already in enough trouble
with my own fan base.

28:27.967 --> 28:30.186
I don't suppose you wanna
take Bulldog?

28:30.230 --> 28:33.276
She's not dangerous.
She's just hurting.

28:33.320 --> 28:35.104
You don't know
this woman.

28:35.148 --> 28:37.498
Okay, just promise me, if she
doesn't want to talk to you,

28:37.541 --> 28:38.542
you'll let it go.

28:39.935 --> 28:41.894
Okay. I will.

28:41.937 --> 28:44.505
Good.
'Cause I love ya.

28:44.548 --> 28:45.898
Oh, my God.

28:45.941 --> 28:47.203
I said "love."

28:47.247 --> 28:49.336
I-I should start
rambling nonsense

28:49.379 --> 28:51.468
and awkwardly back out
the door like this.

28:51.512 --> 28:53.209
This is how you do it,
right?

28:53.253 --> 28:54.689
Peace
to all of humanity.

28:54.733 --> 28:57.431
[ Chuckles ] Very funny.

28:57.474 --> 29:01.348
There's just
one difference.

29:01.391 --> 29:03.350
You know, when I said "love ya"
just then,

29:03.393 --> 29:05.482
I didn't say it
in some universal,

29:05.526 --> 29:07.746
all-of-humanity way.

29:07.789 --> 29:10.749
I said it in a very,
very personal way.

29:10.792 --> 29:13.273
Like this...

29:13.316 --> 29:15.666
I love you.

29:15.710 --> 29:17.930
I love you, too.

29:17.973 --> 29:23.587
♪♪

29:23.631 --> 29:26.155
Thank you.

29:26.199 --> 29:29.115
You figured out what
was going on with him
in like two seconds.

29:29.158 --> 29:31.378
I used to read
"Encyclopedia Brown"

29:31.421 --> 29:33.467
when I was a kid,

29:33.510 --> 29:38.341
and the map for World War I
was labeled "World War I."

29:38.385 --> 29:39.995
How'd they know there was
gonna be a second world war?

29:40.039 --> 29:41.562
[ Chuckles ]

29:41.605 --> 29:44.957
And you're funny, and you helped
Darcy with her PTSD,

29:45.000 --> 29:48.569
and you were willing to
move to Lenox.

29:53.095 --> 29:54.967
Why'd you two break up,
anyway?

29:57.186 --> 29:58.492
She didn't tell you,
huh?

29:58.535 --> 29:59.623
No.

30:01.712 --> 30:06.065
Well, the truth is,

30:06.108 --> 30:09.851
she realized she wanted to
give you two another shot.

30:11.766 --> 30:14.769
Sometimes two people are just
meant to be together,

30:14.813 --> 30:19.339
and no matter
what you do,

30:19.382 --> 30:21.428
the universe finds a way
to make it happen.

30:21.471 --> 30:30.654
♪♪

30:30.698 --> 30:33.309
You know what? Um,
I'm gonna use the bathroom.

30:33.353 --> 30:34.528
If you lock yourself
in there,

30:34.571 --> 30:36.138
I'm gonna tear the door
off the hinges.

30:36.182 --> 30:37.357
With what screwdriver?

30:37.400 --> 30:38.575
[ Chuckles ]

30:38.619 --> 30:40.621
Hey, uh, Gary,
can I...

30:40.664 --> 30:42.144
can I ask you something?

30:44.103 --> 30:46.061
Did --
Did you miss me at all?

30:47.062 --> 30:48.237
What?

30:48.281 --> 30:51.937
I mean, I know you and my mom
broke up,

30:51.980 --> 30:57.333
but I didn't know that meant
we couldn't be friends anymore.

30:57.377 --> 30:58.900
Dude...

31:01.468 --> 31:05.385
...not a day has gone by
that I haven't missed you.

31:06.908 --> 31:08.301
And just so you know,

31:08.344 --> 31:10.781
I needed today just as badly
as you did.

31:10.825 --> 31:12.696
Probably even more.

31:12.740 --> 31:14.350
I'm so happy
you came to visit me,

31:14.394 --> 31:16.613
because there's
something very special

31:16.657 --> 31:17.963
that I want to give you.

31:18.006 --> 31:24.360
♪♪

31:24.404 --> 31:28.930
Wherever you go,
whether we're together or not,

31:28.974 --> 31:32.238
when you wear this,
I'm with you.

31:32.281 --> 31:35.415
But that's
your lucky hat.

31:35.458 --> 31:37.112
Are you sure you want me
to have it?

31:37.156 --> 31:38.157
I'm positive.

31:38.200 --> 31:41.987
And now it is
your lucky hat.

31:42.030 --> 31:45.947
♪♪

31:45.991 --> 31:48.123
Are you sure
this is okay?

31:48.167 --> 31:49.951
It's more than okay.

31:49.995 --> 31:55.087
♪♪

31:55.130 --> 32:00.266
♪♪

32:00.309 --> 32:01.484
You ready, pal?

32:01.528 --> 32:03.008
Yep.
Sure is.

32:03.051 --> 32:04.966
Time to hit the road.

32:05.010 --> 32:07.142
You fellas drive safe.

32:07.186 --> 32:12.321
♪♪

32:12.365 --> 32:14.106
Bye, Gary.

32:14.149 --> 32:15.585
Goodbye, Liam.

32:15.629 --> 32:21.635
♪♪

32:21.678 --> 32:23.985
[ Door closes ]

32:24.029 --> 32:26.205
You missed her
by 20 minutes.

32:26.248 --> 32:28.642
She was putting Charlie down
for like the fourth time,

32:28.685 --> 32:30.600
and then she finally
crashed, too.

32:30.644 --> 32:32.298
Well, I'm glad you're up.

32:32.341 --> 32:33.429
You're lucky Milo and I

32:33.473 --> 32:35.301
are binge-watching
"My So-Called Life."

32:35.344 --> 32:36.650
Wait, isn't he here?

32:36.693 --> 32:38.478
Unfortunately, yes,

32:38.521 --> 32:40.741
which is why we just
get on a video chat,

32:40.784 --> 32:42.525
sync up our computers,

32:42.569 --> 32:45.398
and then press "play"
at the exact same time.

32:45.441 --> 32:47.922
For a few minutes, it doesn't
feel like we're an ocean apart.

32:49.489 --> 32:52.535
So, um,
what is the big news?

32:52.579 --> 32:54.885
I got into MMI.

32:54.929 --> 32:56.278
Of course you got in!

32:56.322 --> 32:58.324
Congratulations!
When do you start?

32:58.367 --> 33:00.848
Yeah, that's actually
my question, too.

33:02.719 --> 33:05.461
I don't know. I just don't feel
like I thought I would.

33:06.636 --> 33:08.943
I've spent the last year
trying to prove

33:08.987 --> 33:10.901
that I could get into
my dream school,

33:10.945 --> 33:13.556
and now that I did,

33:13.600 --> 33:16.429
just realizing maybe it's not
my dream anymore.

33:16.472 --> 33:19.388
Okay.

33:19.432 --> 33:22.957
But if that's not your dream,
then what is?

33:28.832 --> 33:31.531
To the first of
many collaborations.

33:31.574 --> 33:33.011
[ Chuckles ]

33:34.490 --> 33:35.709
You know
you have to drink it

33:35.752 --> 33:36.753
for the toast
to work, right?

33:36.797 --> 33:38.016
[ Clears throat ]

33:41.323 --> 33:42.890
Everything okay?

33:42.933 --> 33:44.805
Yeah, yeah.
I just --

33:44.848 --> 33:46.502
It's a lot to take in.

33:48.896 --> 33:50.724
You brought my film back
from the dead.

33:50.767 --> 33:52.639
That was all you.

33:52.682 --> 33:54.728
I'm just happy to be
riding your coattails.

33:54.771 --> 33:57.078
[ Both laugh ]

33:57.122 --> 33:58.558
What are we celebrating
tonight?

33:58.601 --> 33:59.820
Anniversary?

33:59.863 --> 34:01.691
No, no. We're just --
We're just friends.

34:01.735 --> 34:03.737
Colleagues, actually.

34:03.780 --> 34:07.523
Um, just colleagues
and just friends.

34:09.569 --> 34:11.179
Glad Gina wasn't here
to hear him say that.

34:11.223 --> 34:13.703
[ Scoffs ]
What do you mean?

34:13.747 --> 34:15.314
Oh, it's nothing.

34:15.357 --> 34:16.924
A-Actually -- Actually,
it's pretty funny.

34:16.967 --> 34:18.186
Gina's got
this crazy idea

34:18.230 --> 34:20.449
that you've got
a little crush on me.

34:20.493 --> 34:21.972
[ Chuckles ]

34:23.887 --> 34:26.194
Well, I wasn't gonna
say anything,

34:26.238 --> 34:29.545
because, you know,
you're married,

34:29.589 --> 34:31.025
but it's not crazy.

34:31.069 --> 34:33.506
What?

34:33.549 --> 34:35.682
I'm attracted to you,

34:35.725 --> 34:38.859
and I kind of assumed
it was mutual.

34:38.902 --> 34:40.643
And look,
if I have the wrong idea

34:40.687 --> 34:41.818
and you are
happily married,

34:41.862 --> 34:44.430
nothing is happening
between us.

34:44.473 --> 34:45.692
♪♪

34:45.735 --> 34:47.998
But I don't know.

34:48.042 --> 34:50.131
♪♪

34:50.175 --> 34:51.959
I just kind of
get the impression

34:52.002 --> 34:55.615
that maybe
you're not that happy.

34:55.658 --> 34:57.182
♪♪

35:01.708 --> 35:10.717
♪♪

35:10.760 --> 35:19.769
♪♪

35:19.813 --> 35:28.865
♪♪

35:28.909 --> 35:37.961
♪♪

35:38.005 --> 35:40.268
[ Groans ]
What's the matter?

35:40.312 --> 35:41.269
Are you gonna throw up?

35:41.313 --> 35:42.531
[ Groans ]

35:42.575 --> 35:43.619
God, every time
I say something nice to you,

35:43.663 --> 35:44.881
you throw up.

35:44.925 --> 35:46.144
It's okay.

35:46.187 --> 35:47.232
I'm not throwing up.

35:49.103 --> 35:50.539
[ Groans ]

35:50.583 --> 35:56.937
♪♪

35:56.980 --> 35:58.156
You're in?

35:58.199 --> 35:59.983
I'm in.

36:00.027 --> 36:05.424
♪♪

36:05.467 --> 36:11.125
♪♪

36:11.169 --> 36:12.735
[ Sighs ]

36:12.779 --> 36:16.913
♪♪

36:16.957 --> 36:19.046
♪ And I'll run to you

36:19.089 --> 36:20.047
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

36:20.090 --> 36:23.703
♪ When the waters rise

36:23.746 --> 36:29.143
♪ And I'll run to you
if the bombs ignite ♪

36:29.187 --> 36:32.320
♪♪

36:32.364 --> 36:35.889
Hey, Bloom.
I was just thinking about you.

36:35.932 --> 36:37.238
What's going on
in your world?

36:37.282 --> 36:41.851
♪ I'll still call to you
if I lose my sight ♪

36:41.895 --> 36:44.114
Hey, sir, do you
happen to drive a minivan?

36:44.158 --> 36:46.769
Because they're about to tow it
for -- for being so cool.

36:46.813 --> 36:48.641
[ Laughs ]

36:48.684 --> 36:50.338
What are you doing here?

36:50.382 --> 36:51.644
Sophie stopped by
the music store

36:51.687 --> 36:54.124
to tell me
she got into MMI

36:54.168 --> 36:57.127
and invited me to crash
the celebration.

36:57.171 --> 36:58.346
Where is she?

36:58.390 --> 37:01.393
Oh, she must be --
wow, running very late.

37:01.436 --> 37:03.177
♪♪

37:03.221 --> 37:06.789
Oh, she's good.

37:06.833 --> 37:08.182
What do you mean?

37:08.226 --> 37:10.663
I think we just got
"Parent Trap"-ed.

37:10.706 --> 37:12.839
♪♪

37:12.882 --> 37:14.971
Oh.
Yeah.

37:15.015 --> 37:16.495
W-Well, lucky for you,

37:16.538 --> 37:19.062
I always had a big crush
on Dennis Quaid.

37:19.106 --> 37:20.629
Who didn't?

37:20.673 --> 37:21.935
Right?
[ Laughs ]

37:24.590 --> 37:29.943
But this is still --
it's pretty complicated, right?

37:29.986 --> 37:32.859
♪♪

37:32.902 --> 37:34.513
Maybe it doesn't
have to be.

37:34.556 --> 37:36.297
♪♪

37:36.341 --> 37:37.255
I'm Eddie.

37:40.040 --> 37:41.433
I'm Anna.

37:41.476 --> 37:44.566
Well, it's nice to finally
meet you.

37:44.610 --> 37:47.308
♪ Using all that we can

37:47.352 --> 37:49.267
Thanks again for
letting me audition.

37:49.310 --> 37:50.355
Of course.

37:50.398 --> 37:52.618
I'm sorry you didn't
get into MMI.

37:52.661 --> 37:54.228
They're idiots
not to want you.

37:54.272 --> 37:55.708
[ Chuckles ] Well, actually,
I did get in,

37:55.751 --> 37:57.884
but I'm not going.

37:57.927 --> 37:59.320
Really?

37:59.364 --> 38:00.669
Really.

38:00.713 --> 38:02.758
'Cause there's something else
I want more.

38:02.802 --> 38:04.282
♪♪

38:04.325 --> 38:05.500
This.

38:05.544 --> 38:07.285
[ Chuckles ]

38:07.328 --> 38:10.766
Which is why I'm here,
betting on myself.

38:10.810 --> 38:12.681
Well, I'm all for that.

38:12.725 --> 38:14.422
Let's see what you got.

38:14.466 --> 38:15.684
♪♪

38:15.728 --> 38:18.426
[ Guitar playing ]

38:18.470 --> 38:24.824
♪♪

38:24.867 --> 38:31.483
♪ All our past and problems
understood ♪

38:31.526 --> 38:37.837
♪♪

38:37.880 --> 38:45.366
♪ If only we would act now
as we could ♪

38:45.410 --> 38:51.372
♪♪

38:51.416 --> 38:57.378
♪♪

38:57.422 --> 39:00.163
Gina, I...

39:00.207 --> 39:01.817
We need to talk.

39:01.861 --> 39:04.472
What happened?

39:04.516 --> 39:06.518
Did they not buy
the movie?

39:06.561 --> 39:08.824
Oh, no, no. They did.

39:08.868 --> 39:13.438
Then...what's going on?

39:13.481 --> 39:15.091
I'm so sorry.

39:16.615 --> 39:18.965
Did something happen
with Cassandra?

39:19.008 --> 39:22.795
No. Nothing happened
between us.

39:22.838 --> 39:25.885
But you were right. She --
She did have feelings for me,

39:25.928 --> 39:27.974
and she thought I did,
too.

39:28.017 --> 39:31.499
And I know why,
because I've been...

39:31.543 --> 39:34.372
♪♪

39:34.415 --> 39:37.636
Rome. Talk to me.

39:37.679 --> 39:40.073
I sold my movie today.

39:40.116 --> 39:42.858
Felt nothing.

39:42.902 --> 39:47.167
When you came home,
I felt nothing.

39:47.210 --> 39:48.734
I've been faking it
for everybody,

39:48.777 --> 39:50.823
trying to make it seem like
I'm great.

39:50.866 --> 39:56.045
♪♪

39:56.089 --> 39:58.004
But I can't fake it
with you.

39:58.047 --> 39:59.788
♪♪

39:59.832 --> 40:02.443
My depression...

40:02.487 --> 40:06.621
♪♪

40:06.665 --> 40:08.144
...it's back.

40:09.929 --> 40:12.105
Come here.

40:12.148 --> 40:13.323
Come here.

40:13.367 --> 40:18.241
♪♪

40:18.285 --> 40:21.636
♪ Using all that we can

40:21.680 --> 40:24.204
♪♪

40:24.247 --> 40:26.859
So you're driving to Albany
to meet your stalker?

40:26.902 --> 40:29.731
Seems like a once-in-a-lifetime
opportunity.

40:29.775 --> 40:33.300
Yeah.If she stabs you, just don't
bleed on my leather seats.

40:33.343 --> 40:35.824
I will be sure to
bleed politely.

40:35.868 --> 40:37.783
Keys.

40:37.826 --> 40:40.263
Thank you.
Gas tank's on --

40:40.307 --> 40:42.527
On the side the arrow
is pointing at. I know.

40:42.570 --> 40:43.745
The A/C should only
be run on --

40:43.789 --> 40:45.268
Recirculation.

40:45.312 --> 40:47.140
Unless you have dairy
without your Lactaid,

40:47.183 --> 40:49.011
in which case,
just crack a window.

40:49.055 --> 40:50.578
And remember,
premium unleaded only.

40:50.622 --> 40:52.101
Oh, my God, Gary.

40:52.145 --> 40:54.364
If you're so worried that
I'm gonna destroy your car,

40:54.408 --> 40:55.801
you might as well just
drive me there yourself.

40:55.844 --> 40:57.411
Well, maybe I will.

41:00.153 --> 41:02.372
I mean, if you want to.

41:02.416 --> 41:04.592
♪♪

41:04.636 --> 41:06.507
I'm in.

41:06.551 --> 41:10.468
♪♪

41:10.511 --> 41:11.817
Alright.

41:11.860 --> 41:16.735
♪ And I'll run to you
when the waters rise ♪

41:16.778 --> 41:23.524
♪ And I'll run to you
if the bombs ignite ♪

41:23.568 --> 41:29.835
♪ I'll still call to you
if I do go blind ♪

41:29.878 --> 41:34.056
♪ And I'll be all for you
if you lose the fight ♪

41:38.887 --> 41:41.237
Hi, I'm Lizzy Greene.
Tonight's episode featured

41:41.281 --> 41:43.109
a mother grieving
over the loss of her son.

41:43.152 --> 41:45.241
If you yourself
have struggled with suicide

41:45.285 --> 41:48.375
or have lost a loved one,
you are not alone.

41:48.418 --> 41:50.203
Please get the help
you deserve and reach out

41:50.246 --> 41:52.597
to the American Foundation
for Suicide Prevention.

41:52.640 --> 41:55.208
Learn more at afsp.org.

42:03.433 --> 42:05.174
You can learn more about suicide

42:05.218 --> 42:07.568
from the American Foundation
for Suicide Prevention

42:07.612 --> 42:09.831
at afsp.org

42:09.875 --> 42:14.444
or by calling 1-800-273-TALK.

42:20.059 --> 42:29.503
♪♪

42:29.547 --> 42:39.208
♪♪

42:39.252 --> 42:48.957
♪♪
